issue.title: `facetStats` for an attribute shouldn't take into account the filters on that attribute
issue.body:
The best example for this would be a `price` attribute and a price range slider on the front-end. When the user sets a min/max value on the range slider, and you send a query with the appropriate filter (e.g. `price >= <min> AND price <= <max>`) to Meilisearch, Meilisearch returns `facetStats` for `price` that's equal to the filter itself. This would be problematic for the front-end, because after the price range slider is updated to match the `facetStats`, then the user can't change the min & max to greater values.

it seems like you have noticed this problem in the the official [E-commerce demo](https://ecommerce.meilisearch.com/), where you are performing a multi-search, with two searches, the second one without the filters, just so that its `price` facet stats would be accurate.
